==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Gallegan'''

# [[Synonym]] for [[Galician]]. Both nouns are Standard English names for citizens of [[Galicia]], and there appears to be no ethnic slur or other pejorative sense attached to [[Gallegan]]. However, Galicians might consider the term [[Gallegan]] offensive because it's based, not upon the original [[autonym]] (or [[endonym]] or auto[[ethnonym]]) ''galego'', but upon the Spanish [[exonym]] ''gallego''.

# '''Galician´s language.''' Name of the language spoken in Galicia, spanish region located at the spanish north-west, limiting whith the north of Portugal. Although this language may sound a mix between spanish and portuguese its a language itself, derived from latin just as spanish, portuguese, catalan or italian for example.

